{"type":"message","id":"5404427e","parentId":"897a8b49","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:03:10.460Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about what files are not being pushed to git. This is a question about the git backup system. Let me recall what I know about the backup system from the MEMORY.md I just read:\n\n- GitHub backup at https://github.com/tempint001-cpu/openclaw-workspace — auto-push every 2h via cron\n- Created backup_verifier.py script to verify memory files are committed and pushed\n- Also from April 6: \"GitHub backup had no verification — created backup_verifier.py script\"\n\nSo there's a verification script that likely checks what's being backed up. The user is asking what files are NOT being pushed. This is a good question - I should check the current git status to see which files are untracked or not committed/pushed.\n\nHowever, I need to be careful. The user might be asking about files that are intentionally excluded (like private data) or files that are just not being tracked. Let me check the git status and also look at the .gitignore to see what's excluded.\n\nI should:\n1. Check current git status to see untracked/modified files\n2. Check .gitignore to see what patterns are excluded\n3. Possibly run the backup_verifier script if it exists to see what it reports\n\nLet me start by checking the git status.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_69df6f0e52ff4f8ebe9c8953","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git status --porcelain=v1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":425,"output":627,"cacheRead":20096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775415783340,"responseId":"gen-1775415783-zpkvkbNevIOmQ67XMqxg"}}
