{"type":"message","id":"4d1fb1aa","parentId":"8ea528c7","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:03:37.139Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect - the branches are identical, no uncommitted changes, no untracked files, and everything is synced with remote.\n\nNow I can answer the user's question clearly. The only files NOT being pushed to git are:\n1. Files explicitly ignored by .gitignore (environment files, secrets, keys, etc.)\n2. Anything untracked (currently nothing)\n3. The .openclaw/ directory (internal to OpenClaw)\n\nLet me give a concise but comprehensive answer.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Short answer: **Only files that shouldn't be in git.** Everything tracked is pushed automatically every 2 hours.\n\n### What's excluded via `.gitignore`:\n- `.env` files (API keys, secrets)\n- `**/*.key` and `**/*.pem` (private keys, certificates)\n- `**/secrets*` (secrets directories)\n- `.openclaw/` (OpenClaw internal)\n- `.DS_Store` (macOS cruft)\n\n### Current status:\n- No uncommitted changes\n- No untracked files\n- Branch is synced with origin (everything pushed)\n\nThat's it — the backup system is clean."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":618,"output":360,"cacheRead":22400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23378,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775415812223,"responseId":"gen-1775415812-OnAXfHqN31ic9RVcEPg7"}}
