led":true,"createdAtMs":1774971606687,"updatedAtMs":1775406658991,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 22 * * *","tz":"Asia/Kolkata"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"FIRST: Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md for context. Send a bedtime story to group via message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639). Story: real historical event or powerful life lesson, 8-12 lines, simple language, something people genuinely love. End with goodnight wish. Search the web for a compelling true story if needed. If fails, message Nemesis at target=7924461837.","model":"kilocode/kilo-auto/free"},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1775493000000,"lastRunAtMs":1775406600005,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":58986,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false}},{"id":"0caabdd4-3d9a-453d-92fd-b052f4f8e44c","name":"weekly-memory-curation","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774980664890,"updatedAtMs":1775338463167,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 3 * * 0","tz":"Asia/Kolkata"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"FIRST: Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Run `date +%Y-%m-%d` for today. 1) List all memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md files. 2) For files older than 30 days, read them, extract anything worth keeping, add to MEMORY.md, then delete the old file. 3) Clean up MEMORY.md — remove stale/outdated entries, keep it under 50 lines. 4) Push to GitHub. 5) Message Nemesis at target=7924461837 with summary of what was cleaned."},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1775943000000,"lastRunAtMs":1775338371927,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":91240,"lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0}},{"id":"ac311486-d2d0-4fad-ac7f-ae54a2649bb0","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:group:-1003606834639","name":"April 27 exam reminder (good morning)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1775322392409,"updatedAtMs":1775322392409,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 8 27 4 *","tz":"Asia/Kolkata"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Send the following exact message to the Nrexya group using message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639): '🌅 Good morning, Nrexya! \\n\\nToday is April 27 — exam day! Wishing everyone the best, especially those with exams. You've prepared well, go crush it! 💪\\n\\nHave a great Saturday! 🖤'","model":"kilocode/kilo-auto/free"},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1777257000000}}],"total":13,"offset":0,"limit":13,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775415889347}}
{"type":"message","id":"b236c8bd","parentId":"48c3b67c","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:04:56.798Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the cron jobs. Let me analyze the health check results:\n\n**Critical issues:**\n1. memory_review: 7582 minutes since last run (threshold 1800 min) - Last: 2026-03-31 12:38 UTC\n   - This corresponds to the \"nightly-memory-review\" job\n   - That job runs at 3 AM Asia/Kolkata (which is 21:30 UTC the previous day)\n   - Last run: 2026-03-31 12:38 UTC - That's 5+ days ago\n   - Current time: 2026-04-05 19:01 UTC\n   - The schedule is `0 3 * * *` in Asia/Kolkata timezone\n\n2. group_message: 937 minutes since last run (threshold 360 min) - Last: 2026-04-05 03:23 UTC\n   - This seems to be related to group message delivery\n   - Looking at the cron jobs, I see several with `delivery.mode: \"none\"` and `channel: \"telegram\", to: \"-1003606834639\"` or similar\n   - But also some with `delivery.mode: \"announce\"` that should send messages\n\n3. git_push: 3279 minutes (~2.3 days) since last run (threshold 360 min) - Last: 2026-04-03 15:21 UTC\n   - This is the \"github-backup\" job\n   - It runs every 2 hours: `0 */2 * * *`\n   - Last run was April 3, now April 5 - so it's been 2 days without running\n\n4. nemesis_ping: 3279 minutes since last run (threshold 480 min) - Last: 2026-04-03 15:21 UTC\n\n\n- I'm seeing potential delivery issues with the backup job\n- The last delivery status shows \"not-delivered\" for earlier jobs\n\nI'll investigate why these jobs are failing. The backup job's delivery mode looks suspicious. I need to check the script and why messages aren't being delivered as expected.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2a9fbabdd51541c391adb644","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"scripts/heartbeat_health_cron.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":5705,"output":886,"cacheRead":22528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29119,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775415889355,"responseId":"gen-1775415889-Hp8ynjS2TMw7T3v6hUbk"}}
{"type":"message","id":"929934ea","parentId":"b236c8bd","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:04:56.819Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2a9fbabdd51541c391adb644","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nHeartbeat Health Monitor - Cron Job\nRuns independently of the heartbeat to verify state is being updated.\nAlerts if heartbeat state becomes stale.\n\nThis should run as a cron job (recommended: every 1 hour).\nIf heartbeat state is stale, it will DM Nemesis with the alert.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 heartbeat_health_cron.py [--dry-run]\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nimport argparse\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSCRIPT_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent\nSTATE_FILE = SCRIPT_DIR / \"memory\" / \"heartbeat-state.json\"\nNEMESIS_ID = \"7924461837\"\n\nTHRESHOLDS = {\n    \"heartbeat_run\": {\"warning\": 45, \"critical\": 60},\n    \"group_message\": {\"warning\": 240, \"critical\": 360},\n    \"nemesis_ping\": {\"warning\": 360, \"critical\": 480},\n    \"git_push\": {\"warning\": 180, \"critical\": 360},\n    \"memory_review\": {\"warning\": 1560, \"critical\": 1800},\n}\n\n\ndef load_state():\n    if not STATE_FILE.exists():\n        return {\"lastChecks\": {}}\n    with open(STATE_FILE, \"r\") as f:\n        return json.load(f)\n\n\ndef minutes_ago(timestamp_str):\n    if not timestamp_str:\n        return None\n    try:\n        last_time = datetime.fromisoformat(timestamp_str.replace(\"Z\", \"+00:00\"))\n        now = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n        return (now - last_time).total_seconds() / 60\n    except:\n        return None\n\n\ndef check_health():\n    state = load_state()\n    last_checks = state.get(\"lastChecks\", {})\n\n    critical = []\n    warnings = []\n\n    for field, thresholds in THRESHOLDS.items():\n        value = last_checks.get(field)\n        minutes = minutes_ago(value)\n\n        if minutes is None:\n            critical.append(f\"{field}: Never run\")\n        elif minutes >= thresholds[\"critical\"]:\n            critical.append(\n                f\"{field}: CRITICAL - {round(minutes)} min since last run (threshold: {thresholds['critical']} min)\"\n            )\n        elif minutes >= thresholds[\"warning\"]:\n            warnings.append(\n                f\"{field}: WARNING - {round(minutes)} min since last run (threshold: {thresholds['warning']} min)\"\n            )\n\n    return critical, warnings\n\n\ndef send_alert(critical, warnings, dry_run=False):\n    \"\"\"Send alert to Nemesis via message tool.\"\"\"\n    timestamp = datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M UTC\")\n\n    message = f\"⚠️ **Heartbeat Health Alert** `{timestamp}`\\n\\n\"\n\n    if critical:\n        message += \"**CRITICAL:**\\n\"\n        for item in critical:\n            message += f\"• {item}\\n\"\n        message += \"\\n\"\n\n    if warnings:\n        message += \"**Warnings:**\\n\"\n        for item in warnings:\n            message += f\"• {item}\\n\"\n\n    message += \"\\n_Script: scripts/heartbeat_health_cron.py_\"\n\n    if dry_run:\n        print(\"DRY RUN - Would send:\")\n        print(message)\n        return\n\n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\",\n        \"gateway\",\n        \"call\",\n        \"message.send\",\n        \"--params\",\n        f'{{\"channel\": \"telegram\", \"target\": \"{NEMESIS_ID}\", \"text\": {json.dumps(message)}}}',\n    ]\n\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=30)\n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            print(f\"Alert sent to {NEMESIS_ID}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Failed to send alert: {result.stderr}\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error sending alert: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Heartbeat Health Monitor Cron\")\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Don't send alerts, just print\"\n    )\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    critical, warnings = check_health()\n\n    if critical or warnings:\n        print(f\"Issues found - Critical: {len(critical)}, Warnings: {len(warnings)}\")\n        for item in critical:\n            print(f\"  ✗ {item}\")\n        for item in warnings:\n            print(f\"  ⚠ {item}\")\n\n        if critical:\n            send_alert(critical, warnings, dry_run=args.dry_run)\n            sys.exit(2)\n    else:\n        print(\"Heartbeat state healthy\")\n        sys.exit(0)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775415896812}}
{"type":"message","id":"7028dc84","parentId":"929934ea","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:05:23.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the heartbeat health monitor. It's a separate cron job that checks the `heartbeat-state.json` file to see if the regular heartbeat checks are running on time.\n\nThe issues are:\n\n1. **memory_review** is failing - it's been 7582 min since last run (5+ days)\n   - This corresponds to the \"nightly-memory-review\" cron job that runs at 3 AM Asia/Kolkata\n   - But looking at its lastRunAtMs: 1775338200006 (April 5, 2026 around 03:30 IST? Let me check the epoch)\n   - Wait, the timestamp from health report says last run: 2026-03-31 12:38 UTC, but the cron state shows lastRunAtMs: 1775338200006\n   - Let me convert: 1775338200006 ms = 1775338200.006 seconds = around April 5, 2026 07:30 UTC? No, let me recalculate.\n   - Epoch calculation: 1775338200006 / 1000 = 1775338200 seconds since epoch\n   - 1775338200 / (60*60*24) = 20555 days roughly, that's way in the future? Something's off. Let me not rely on that.\n   - The health report explicitly states: \"Last: 2026-03-31 12:38 UTC\" for memory_review. That's 5+ days ago.\n   - So the nightly-memory-review job is NOT running (or failing silently).\n\n2. **group_message** - 937 minutes ~15.6 hours since last run\n   - This tracks when the last group message was sent\n   - This is updated by the heartbeat when it sends group messages\n   - Last group message in daily log: at 17:16 IST (April 5), which is ~11:46 UTC? Let's convert: 17:16 IST = 11:46 UTC (since IST is UTC+5:30). That's about 7.5 hours ago from 19:01 UTC. But the health report says 937 minutes = 15.6 hours, so it's even older. Could be that the heartbeat hasn't been updating the state properly.\n\n3. **git_push** - 3279 minutes ~2.3 days\n   - This corresponds to the \"github-backup\" cron job\n   - Last run: 2026-04-03 15:21 UTC\n   - Today is April 5, so it's been 2 days without running\n   - But cron shows lastRunAtMs: 1775412080669 which is recent? Wait that seems to be April 5 around 18:34 UTC? Let's recalc: 1775412080669 / 1000 = 1775412080.669 seconds. That's about April 5, 2026 ~ 8:30 PM UTC? Actually 1775412080 / 86400 = 20556 days... that's wrong.\n   - Let me convert properly: Use online mental: April 5, 2026 00:00 UTC is about 1775332800? Not sure.\n   - Let's not rely on raw timestamps. The health report is authoritative: it's been 3279 minutes (2.3 days) since git_push.\n   - So the github-backup job is not running as expected.\n\n4. **nemesis_ping** - 3279 minutes ~2.3 days\n   - This tracks when Nexa last pinged Nemesis in DM\n   - Also last seen 2.3 days ago\n   - This is updated by the heartbeat when it pings Nemesis\n\nSo the core issue is that **heartbeats are not running**, or they are running but failing to update state properly, OR the cron job that triggers heartbeats is not running.\n\nLet's check the actual heartbeat mechanism: The heartbeat runs every 30 min during active hours (7 AM - 11 PM IST). That's managed by the OpenClaw gateway's built-in heartbeat poll, not a cron job. Actually, the HEARTBEAT.md describes a poll that comes from the system. So the heartbeat itself is triggered by OpenClaw, not by cron. The state is updated manually by the agent after each check.\n\nThe health monitor cron runs hourly and checks if the heartbeat state has been updated recently. The fact that it's reporting all these fields as stale indicates that the heartbeat hasn't been updating the state file for many hours/days.\n\nPossible causes:\n- Heartbeat poll is not being triggered (maybe OpenClaw gateway not running? But it's running since we're having this conversation)\n- The heartbeat code is failing silently\n- State file is not being written due to permissions or errors\n- The heartbeat hasn't been active because the workspace hasn't had activity? But we are in a session now.\n\nLet me check the current time in IST: 7:01 PM UTC is 12:31 AM IST next day? Wait: UTC 19:01, IST = UTC+5:30 = 00:31 (next day). So it's after midnight in IST. Heartbeat runs 7 AM - 11 PM IST, so currently outside active window. That could mean heartbeats aren't expected right now.\n\nBut the health monitor says `memory_review` hasn't run since March 31 - that's a cron job, not heartbeat. So that cron job itself is failing, not just heartbeat.\n\nLet's examine each failing cron job individually:\n\n**1. nightly-memory-review** - runs at 3 AM Asia/Kolkata\n   - Last successful run: according to the cron state, lastRunAtMs: 1775338200006. Let's try to decode: 1775338200 seconds since epoch. Using a quick approximation: Unix epoch started 1970-01-01. Current date 2026-04-05 is around 1775318400? Actually, let's compute days: from 1970 to 2026 is 56 years, including leap years. Roughly 56*365.25 = 20454 days. 20454*86400 = 1765241600. That's too low. Let me get more accurate: 2026-04-05 00:00 UTC is 1775376000? Not sure. I'll avoid mental math and just trust the health report: last run March 31, that's 5 days ago. So it's not running.\n\n**2. github-backup** - runs every 2 hours: `0 */2 * * *`\n   - Health report: last run April 3, 2+ days ago. So it's not running.\n\n**3. group_message and nemesis_ping** are heartbeat state fields, not cron jobs. They track when the heartbeat last performed those actions. If heartbeat hasn't been running (maybe because the OpenClaw gateway process is down or not polling?), then these timestamps will be old. But we are in a session now, so OpenClaw is running. However, the heartbeat might not have been triggered during off-hours. The thresholds: group_message critical at 360 min (6h), nemesis_ping critical at 480 min (8h). Since it's currently 00:31 IST (just past midnight), the last heartbeat that would have updated these was likely around 10:30 PM IST (5.5 hours ago) or earlier. But the health report says 3279 minutes (~2.3 days) for both, which suggests that the heartbeat hasn't been running for days, not just since last night.\n\nSo the root cause appears to be: The heartbeat mechanism itself is not updating state, likely because the state file write is failing or the heartbeat checks are not executing. However, we are in a session, which means the gateway is alive. So maybe the heartbeat poll is not configured or disabled? Let's check the config.\n\nWait: The HEARTBEAT.md says: \"When you receive a heartbeat poll, don't just reply silently every time. Use heartbeats productively!\" So the OpenClaw gateway sends heartbeat polls to the agent at intervals. That's part of the system. So if the gateway is running, it should be sending polls. But perhaps the gateway's heartbeat feature is disabled or misconfigured.\n\nLet me check the OpenClaw config for heartbeat settings. But I should focus on immediate fixes.\n\n**Immediate plan:**\n\nFirst, I need to understand why the cron jobs are not running. Are they actually scheduled to run but failing, or not being triggered at all? Let's manually trigger each failing cron job to see if they work.\n\nBut the health report says \"All health checks are in CRITICAL status\" and \"System state is severely stale.\" I should probably:\n\n1. Check the gateway status to see if it's running.\n2. Check the cron scheduler status.\n3. Run the failing cron jobs manually to diagnose errors.\n4. Fix any issues preventing them from running automatically.\n\nLet's start with gateway status.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cb87a188886846ae98868364","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"status"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":1897,"output":3796,"cacheRead":27904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33597,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775415896820,"responseId":"gen-1775415897-uXp6foXNFf4DVeBlH8bX"}}
