{"type":"message","id":"6dc4073e","parentId":"19789ea4","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:05:30.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway tool doesn't have a \"status\" action. Let me check the gateway tool schema: It has actions: restart, config.get, config.schema.lookup, config.apply, config.patch, update.run. So I can't check gateway status directly. But I can check if processes are running or use other means.\n\nMaybe I should read the cron health check script to see what exactly it checks. I already did that. It loads heartbeat-state.json and checks timestamps.\n\nI need to verify if the heartbeat-state.json file exists and is being updated. Let me read it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_503550ffde234b1cac7da1ad","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":2346,"output":286,"cacheRead":29440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32072,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775415923409,"responseId":"gen-1775415924-iN5Xol4ea6WhfX4l4nh8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"81a36131","parentId":"6dc4073e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:05:30.667Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_503550ffde234b1cac7da1ad","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"lastChecks\": {\n    \"memory_review\": \"2026-03-31T12:38:00Z\",\n    \"group_message\": \"2026-04-05T03:23:00Z\",\n    \"git_push\": \"2026-04-03T15:21:00Z\",\n    \"nemesis_ping\": \"2026-04-03T15:21:00Z\"\n  }\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775415930657}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f76331a","parentId":"81a36131","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:05:35.656Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The state file confirms the timestamps from the health report. So the state hasn't been updated since those dates.\n\nNow I need to figure out why the heartbeat checks aren't updating this file.\n\nThe heartbeat is executed when OpenClaw sends a poll to the agent. The agent (Nexa) is supposed to read the poll, perform checks, and then run the heartbeat-state-manager script to update the state. That script is mentioned in HEARTBEAT.md as a mandatory last step.\n\nSo maybe the agent hasn't been receiving polls? Or the state update script is failing? Let's check if that script exists.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1ee2f27feed8470d9463ce13","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"skills/heartbeat-state-manager/scripts/update_state.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":555,"output":313,"cacheRead":31488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32356,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775415930668,"responseId":"gen-1775415931-jaxehAptjquYDboMGxjV"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dadc8456","parentId":"5f76331a","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:05:35.676Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1ee2f27feed8470d9463ce13","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nUpdate heartbeat state field(s) in heartbeat-state.json\nUsage: update_state.py --field field_name [--field field_name ...]\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport argparse\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef get_state_file():\n    return Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"memory\" / \"heartbeat-state.json\"\n\n\ndef load_state():\n    state_file = get_state_file()\n\n    if state_file.exists():\n        with open(state_file, \"r\") as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n\n    return {\"lastChecks\": {}}\n\n\ndef save_state(state):\n    state_file = get_state_file()\n    state_file.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    with open(state_file, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(state, f, indent=2)\n\n\ndef update_fields(fields):\n    state = load_state()\n    now = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n\n    for field in fields:\n        if field not in state[\"lastChecks\"]:\n            state[\"lastChecks\"][field] = None\n\n        state[\"lastChecks\"][field] = now\n\n    save_state(state)\n\n    print(f\"Updated: {', '.join(fields)}\")\n    print(f\"Timestamp: {now}\")\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Update heartbeat state\")\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--field\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        required=True,\n        help=\"Field to update (can be specified multiple times)\",\n    )\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    update_fields(args.field)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775415935668}}
{"type":"message","id":"fe16f116","parentId":"dadc8456","timestamp":"2026-04-05T19:05:42.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The update_state.py script seems fine. It's a simple JSON update. It should work if called.\n\nNow, the HEARTBEAT.md says the agent must run this script as the last step after each heartbeat. So why hasn't it been called? Possibly because the agent hasn't been receiving heartbeat polls for days.\n\nBut we're in a session now, which suggests the gateway is alive. However, the heartbeat poll is a separate mechanism that periodically sends a \"heartbeat\" event to the agent. That might be disabled or the gateway's polling might be off.\n\nLet's check the OpenClaw config for heartbeat settings. I can use gateway config.get to see.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f38bb3e0a9e048b3927c1db1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.get","path":"heartbeat"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":830,"output":334,"cacheRead":31744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32908,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775415935677,"responseId":"gen-1775415936-yAv2LTltgQdLHidnm2DO"}}
