{"type":"message","id":"7a860d4b","parentId":"7ac29280","timestamp":"2026-04-06T08:43:41.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, the user is asking me to check the group messages because due to API limit error, I was not able to respond properly. They likely mean that I didn't respond to something in the group chat due to hitting an API rate limit.\n\nLet me check the group messages to see what I missed or failed to respond to. First, I should read the recent group messages from the Nrexya group. The group ID is -1003606834639. I can use the message tool to fetch history or maybe check the cron health monitor output from earlier which mentioned API limit errors.\n\nActually, I should look at the cron health monitor output from earlier in the conversation. I recall seeing something about OpenRouter API limit exceeded. Let me search back in the conversation.\n\nActually, I can check the group messages by using the message tool with action to fetch history? Or I can check if there were any mentions or messages that I should have responded to.\n\nBut the user specifically says: \"check the group mssgs, due to api limit error u were not able to respond properly\"\n\nThis suggests that there was an API limit error that prevented me from responding properly in the group chat. I should check the group for any messages that required a response that I might have missed.\n\nLet me fetch recent group messages. I'll use the message tool to get history from the group. However, the message tool doesn't have a direct \"get history\" action - I think I need to use sessions_history or something? Actually, for getting chat history, I might need to use the message tool with some parameters, but looking at the tool schema, there's no direct \"get\" for history. I can use sessions_history if I know the session key for the group chat.\n\nAlternatively, I can check the cron health monitor script output or look at GROUP.md for recent activity. But