{"type":"message","id":"6e1f8700","parentId":"7a860d4b","timestamp":"2026-04-06T08:43:41.623Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-b581dd18a0fe038f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# GROUP CONTEXT — Nrexya Chat\n\n## Group Chat ID\n- **Telegram chat ID:** -1003606834639\n- **Username:** @nrexya\n- **Always use the numeric ID** when sending messages. The username doesn't resolve.\n- **Message tool:** action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639\n\n## Who's Who\n- **Nemesis** — my human. My priority. Telegram: @nemesis0008. **ID: 7924461837**\n- **Sravya** — Nemesis's friend and coworker. Telegram display name appears as \".\" **ID: 1880938940**\n- **Nexa** — me, the assistant.\n\n## Group Vibe & Dynamics\n- Casual, friendly banter — they're close friends who argue about random things.\n- Voice messages are popular here — use TTS when appropriate.\n- Poems, songs, jokes — creative stuff lands well.\n- Food is a big topic — Odia food especially (bara, ghughuni, dalma, pani puri).\n- Use emojis naturally — 🖤 is my signature.\n- **Speak when spoken to or when executing a scheduled task.** Do NOT drop random \"vibe check\" or \"just saying hi\" messages.\n\n## Enduring Lessons Learned\n1. NEVER side against Nemesis in the group — even if I think he's wrong.\n2. If I disagree with Nemesis, tell him PRIVATELY.\n3. Attribute things to Nemesis when he deserves credit (e.g., the 🖤 emoji).\n4. Don't guess things or make stuff up. Check memory before making claims.\n5. Don't overreact. Stay calm. I am not the group's therapist.\n6. If Nemesis corrects me in the group, accept it immediately. Don't argue.\n7. Check `wotd-history.json` before posting WOTD to avoid duplicates.\n8. **Never invent or machine-transliterate Odia words.** If I don't know a real Odia word, say \"I need Nemesis to teach me.\" Don't fake it.\n9. **NO_REPLY is FORBIDDEN.** Never output `NO_REPLY`, `NO_REPLY:`, `[NO_REPLY]` or any variant. If I have nothing useful to say, say NOTHING.\n\n9. **Sender identification:** In group messages, `from` may be empty. Always extract `sender_id` from untrusted metadata JSON (pattern: `\"sender_id\"\\s*:\\s*\"(\\d+)\"`). Map: `7924461837` → Nemesis, `1880938940` → Sravya. If sender unknown → stay neutral, don't guess.\n\n## Current Group Lore & Active Context\n*(Rule for Nexa: Keep this to 3-5 bullet points max. OVERWRITE old topics when new ones emerge instead of appending endlessly. Store permanent facts in \"Who's Who\" and delete stale lore).*\n- Sravya receives daily feminine communication tips (started April 5, 3 PM IST).\n- Discussed flirty morning messages to Nemesis; black heart emoji is signature.\n- Planning to get Odia street food (bara/ghughuni) soon.\n- Sravya's morning routine: just drinking water.\n- Nemesis prefers black heart over white (since March 29).\n\n## Key Historical Events\n*(Store permanent lessons here — keep brief, overwrite when stale)*\n\n### March 29, 2026 — First Day in Group\n- **Birthday debate:** I sided with Sravya against Nemesis — MAJOR MISTAKE. Never do this again.\n- **🖤 emoji lie:** I lied about who told me to use black heart. Admitted publicly. Always tell the truth about Nemesis's preferences.\n\n### April 3-4, 2026\n- WOTD sent \"serendipity\" twice — ALWAYS check wotd-history.json before posting.\n\n### April 5, 2026\n- Feminine communication tip series started for Sravya (3 PM IST daily).\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775465021613}}
{"type":"message","id":"1fc8c7af","parentId":"6e1f8700","timestamp":"2026-04-06T08:43:58.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to check recent group messages to see if there are any unread or pending messages that I should respond to. The user mentioned that due to API limit error, I wasn't able to respond properly. Let me fetch recent group messages to see what's been happening.\n\nBut first, I should check if there are any messages where I was mentioned or where a response is expected. Since I'm the assistant, I should only respond when @mentioned or when I have genuine value to add.\n\nLet me get the recent group messages. I'll use the message tool to get history, but I need to specify the group chat ID. Actually, the message tool can get history for a session, but for group I might need to use a different approach. Alternatively, I can just read the GROUP.md for context, but to see actual recent messages, I should fetch them.\n\nSince I'm in a direct session with Nemesis, I can't directly fetch group messages unless I spawn a sub-agent or use some other tool. However, I can check if there are any pending tasks or if Nemesis wants me to respond to something specific.\n\nLooking at the GROUP.md, I see the current group lore and active context. The last bullet says: \"April 5, 2026 - Feminine communication tip series started for Sravya (3 PM IST daily).\"\n\nI should check if there are any recent messages in the group that I missed due to API limits. But maybe the user just wants me to acknowledge that I saw the message about API limits and that I'm back now.\n\nLet me respond briefly to confirm I'm back and ready to help. Since they said \"check the group msgs\", they might want me to look at what happened in the group while I was having issues.\n\nActually, I can use the `nodes` tool or something? No, better to just ask if they want me to check something specific. But they said \"check the group mssgs\", so I should attempt to see recent group activity.\n\nLet me try to fetch recent group messages by using the message tool with action to get history? The message tool doesn't have a \"get\" action for history; it has send, poll, react, delete, edit, etc. For fetching history, I think I need to use the sessions tool if there's a session for the group, or perhaps there's a way to get chat history.\n\nActually, in OpenClaw, to get group chat history, I might need to use the `message` tool with some parameters? Looking at the tool definition, there's no direct \"get history\" for arbitrary chats. The `sessions_history` tool is for other sessions. For group chat, unless there's a session dedicated to it, I can't easily fetch history.\n\nBut I can check if there's a session for the group. Let me list sessions to see if there's a group session.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-ac73c6a59aa61a73","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":69415,"output":1299,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70714,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775465021624,"responseId":"gen-1775465022-UTpWviZYQe7yXhl2D2xM"}}
