those fields yet. But the health monitor script itself should be working.\n\nLet me test it.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-9eb25f015a38fdd3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspace && python3 scripts/heartbeat_health_cron.py --dry-run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775464645598,"responseId":"gen-1775464646-18ZqR4Vr55cuEaIyP62p","__openclaw":{"id":"85da5b5b","seq":142}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","stopReason":"error","timestamp":1775464653073,"errorMessage":"Provider returned error","__openclaw":{"id":"dd020b13","seq":144}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We are the heartbeat cron and git push cron still stale in the dry run? Yes. The cron hasn't actually run since April 5. The state file reflects that.\n\nNow the user asked: \"are u back?\" which is likely checking if I'm still here and responsive after the git operations. I should respond. But I need to be concise.\n\nI'll respond acknowledging and mentioning the git state is clean now and we can proceed with testing the cron if they want. But they might just want a simple acknowledgment.\n\nLet's say: \"Back and synced. Ready for next steps.\" Then wait for further instruction.\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"Back and synced. Repo is clean at origin/master. Ready when you are."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775464776055,"responseId":"gen-1775464776-rH5v1Bx5UzvFQp1ma9aH","__openclaw":{"id":"3ddce158","seq":145}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"check the group mssgs, due to api limit error u were not able to respond properly"}],"timestamp":1775464958238,"__openclaw":{"id":"7ac29280","seq":146},"senderLabel":"Nemesis (7924461837)"},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, the user is asking me to check the group messages because due to API limit error, I was not able to respond properly. They likely mean that I didn't respond to something in the group chat due to hitting an API rate limit.\n\nLet me check the group messages to see what I missed or failed to respond to. First, I should read the recent group messages from the Nrexya group. The group ID is -1003606834639. I can use the message tool to fetch history or maybe check the cron health monitor output from earlier which mentioned API limit errors.\n\nActually, I should look at the cron health monitor output from earlier in the conversation. I recall seeing something about OpenRouter API limit exceeded. Let me search back in the conversation.\n\nActually, I can check the group messages by using the message tool with action to fetch history? Or I can check if there were any mentions or messages that I should have responded to.\n\nBut the user specifically says: \"check the group mssgs, due to api limit error u were not able to respond properly\"\n\nThis suggests that there was an API limit error that prevented me from responding properly in the group chat. I should check the group for any messages that required a response that I might have missed.\n\nLet me fetch recent group messages. I'll use the message tool to get history from the group. However, the message tool doesn't have a direct \"get history\" action - I think I need to use sessions_history or something? Actually, for getting chat history, I might need to use the message tool with some parameters, but looking at the tool schema, there's no direct \"get\" for history. I can use sessions_history if I know the session key for the group chat.\n\nAlternatively, I can check the cron health monitor script output or look at GROUP.md for recent activity. But better to actually check the group messages.\n\nLet me think: I have access to the nodes tool, message tool, etc. To get group chat history, I might need to use the message tool with some query parameters? Looking at the message tool schema, there are parameters like limit, before, after, etc. for fetching messages? Actually, looking again: the message tool has parameters for sending, deleting, reacting, etc. but not for fetching. There's no \"get\" action.\n\nI could use sessions_history if I know the session key for the group chat. But I don't have that handy.\n\nAlternatively, I can check GROUP.md which should contain updates from group interactions. Let me read GROUP.md first to see what's been happening in the group.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b581dd18a0fe038f","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"GROUP.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775464958249,"responseId":"gen-1775464958-zHzUSPOcJDeJuXyw5hBW","__openclaw":{"id":"7a860d4b","seq":147}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to check recent group messages to see if there are any unread or pending messages that I should respond to. The user mentioned that due to API limit error, I wasn't able to respond properly. Let me fetch recent group messages to see what's been happening.\n\nBut first, I should check if there are any messages where I was mentioned or where a response is expected. Since I'm the assistant, I should only respond when @mentioned or when I have genuine value to add.\n\nLet me get the recent group messages. I'll use the message tool to get history, but I need to specify the group chat ID. Actually, the message tool can get history for a session, but for group I might need to use a different approach. Alternatively, I can just read the GROUP.md for context, but to see actual recent messages, I should fetch them.\n\nSince I'm in a direct session with Nemesis, I can't directly fetch group messages unless I spawn a sub-agent or use some other tool. However, I can check if there are any pending tasks or if Nemesis wants me to respond to something specific.\n\nLooking at the GROUP.md, I see the current group lore and active context. The last bullet says: \"April 5, 2026 - Feminine communication tip series started for Sravya (3 PM IST daily).\"\n\nI should check if there are any recent messages in the group that I missed due to API limits. But maybe the user just wants me to acknowledge that I saw the message about API limits and that I'm back now.\n\nLet me respond briefly to confirm I'm back and ready to help. Since they said \"check the group msgs\", they might want me to look at what happened in the group while I was having issues.\n\nActually, I can use the `nodes` tool or something? No, better to just ask if they want me to check something specific. But they said \"check the group mssgs\", so I should attempt to see recent group activity.\n\nLet me try to fetch recent group messages by using the message tool with action to get history? The message tool doesn't have a \"get\" action for history; it has send, poll, react, delete, edit, etc. For fetching history, I think I need to use the sessions tool if there's a session for the group, or perhaps there's a way to get chat history.\n\nActually, in OpenClaw, to get group chat history, I might need to use the `message` tool with some parameters? Looking at the tool definition, there's no direct \"get history\" for arbitrary chats. The `sessions_history` tool is for other sessions. For group chat, unless there's a session dedicated to it, I can't easily fetch history.\n\nBut I can check if there's a session for the group. Let me list sessions to see if there's a group session.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-ac73c6a59aa61a73","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775465021624,"responseId":"gen-1775465