{"type":"message","id":"2eff5f13","parentId":"ffda145b","timestamp":"2026-04-06T08:44:44.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the cron health monitor output from earlier to see if there were API limit errors mentioned. I recall seeing something about OpenRouter API limit exceeded. Let me look back at the conversation.\n\nActually, I can check the group messages by using the message tool with action to fetch history? Or I can check if there were any mentions or messages that I should have responded to.\n\nBut the user specifically says: \"check the group mssgs, due to api limit error u were not able to respond properly\"\n\nThis suggests that there was an API limit error that prevented me from responding properly in the group chat. I should check the group for any messages that required a response that I might have missed.\n\nLet me fetch recent group messages. I'll use the message tool to get history from the group. However, the message tool doesn't have a direct \"get history\" action - I think I need to use sessions_history or something? Actually, for getting chat history, I might need to use the message tool with some parameters, but looking at the tool schema, there's no direct \"get\" for history. I can use sessions_history if I know the session key for the group chat.\n\nAlternatively, I can check the cron health monitor script output or look at GROUP.md for recent activity. But better to actually check the group messages.\n\nLet me think: I have access to the nodes tool, message tool, etc. To get group chat history, I might need to use the message tool with some query parameters? Looking at the message tool schema, there are parameters like limit, before, after, etc. for fetching messages? Actually, looking again: the message tool has parameters for sending, deleting, reacting, etc. but not for fetching. There's no \"get\" action.\n\nI could use sessions_history if I know the session key for the group chat