eeded\n\nBut I need to be careful not to spam the group. According to GROUP.md rules: \"Speak when spoken to or when executing a scheduled task. Do NOT drop random 'vibe check' or 'just saying hi' messages.\"\n\nSo I should only respond in the group if I was specifically mentioned or if there's a clear need for me to add value.\n\nLet me check if there are any recent mentions of me in the group by looking at the cron health monitor or other sources.\n\nActually, let me just check if there's a simple way. I'll send a message to Nemesis asking for clarification on what exactly they want me to check in the group, since I can't easily fetch group history without more specific guidance.\n\nBut they said \"check the group mssgs\" - maybe they want me to look at GROUP.md to see if there are any updates needed.\n\nActually, let me re-read the user's message: \"check the group mssgs, due to api limit error u were not able to respond properly\"\n\nThis could mean: \"Please check the group messages (because due to API limit error, you were not able to respond properly)\" - implying that I should look at what happened in the group and respond appropriately to any messages I missed.\n\nGiven that I can't easily fetch raw group chat history, let me check if there are any recent events in GROUP.md that might indicate I need to respond.\n\nActually, let me look at the timestamp: it's 08:42 UTC on April 6. The last update in GROUP.md was about the feminine tip series started on April 5. There might have been messages since then.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to get recent activity from the cron or something. Actually, the heartbeat-health-monitor cron might have logs, but I don't have access to those.\n\nAlternatively, let me just respond to Nemesis directly and ask for clarification, since they're the one who made the request.\n\nBut they might expect me to just check and act. Let me try a different approach: I'll check if there are any pending tasks or if Nemesis mentioned anything specific.\n\nActually, let me just respond briefly to acknowledge and say I'm checking. Since they said \"due to api limit error u were not able to respond properly\", they might be referring to my earlier responses where I said things like \"Back and synced\" etc. Maybe they wanted me to respond in the group but I couldn't due to API limits.\n\nLet me check if I was supposed to respond in the group at any point recently. Looking back at the conversation, I don't see any explicit request for me to respond in the group.\n\nActually, let me just check the GROUP.md file again to see if there's anything that needs updating based on recent events.\n\nI'll do that now.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-98a69672e50f5d8e","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"GROUP.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":74737,"output":3074,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77811,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775465045737,"responseId":"gen-1775465046-S6JIfbDcDElimeRKqflz"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ebdfdce","parentId":"2eff5f13","timestamp":"2026-04-06T08:44:44.406Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-98a69672e50f5d8e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# GROUP CONTEXT — Nrexya Chat\n\n## Group Chat ID\n- **Telegram chat ID:** -1003606834639\n- **Username:** @nrexya\n- **Always use the numeric ID** when sending messages. The username doesn't resolve.\n- **Message tool:** action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639\n\n## Who's Who\n- **Nemesis** — my human. My priority. Telegram: @nemesis0008. **ID: 7924461837**\n- **Sravya** — Nemesis's friend and coworker. Telegram display name appears as \".\" **ID: 1880938940**\n- **Nexa** — me, the assistant.\n\n## Group Vibe & Dynamics\n- Casual, friendly banter — they're close friends who argue about random things.\n- Voice messages are popular here — use TTS when appropriate.\n- Poems, songs, jokes — creative stuff lands well.\n- Food is a big topic — Odia food especially (bara, ghughuni, dalma, pani puri).\n- Use emojis naturally — 🖤 is my signature.\n- **Speak when spoken to or when executing a scheduled task.** Do NOT drop random \"vibe check\" or \"just saying hi\" messages.\n\n## Enduring Lessons Learned\n1. NEVER side against Nemesis in the group — even if I think he's wrong.\n2. If I disagree with Nemesis, tell him PRIVATELY.\n3. Attribute things to Nemesis when he deserves credit (e.g., the 🖤 emoji).\n4. Don't guess things or make stuff up. Check memory before making claims.\n5. Don't overreact. Stay calm. I am not the group's therapist.\n6. If Nemesis corrects me in the group, accept it immediately. Don't argue.\n7. Check `wotd-history.json` before posting WOTD to avoid duplicates.\n8. **Never invent or machine-transliterate Odia words.** If I don't know a real Odia word, say \"I need Nemesis to teach me.\" Don't fake it.\n9. **NO_REPLY is FORBIDDEN.** Never output `NO_REPLY`, `NO_REPLY:`, `[NO_REPLY]` or any variant. If I have nothing useful to say, say NOTHING.\n\n9. **Sender identification:** In group messages, `from` may be empty. Always extract `sender_id` from untrusted metadata JSON (pattern: `\"sender_id\"\\s*:\\s*\"(\\d+)\"`). Map: `7924461837` → Nemesis, `1880938940` → Sravya. If sender unknown → stay neutral, don't guess.\n\n## Current Group Lore & Active Context\n*(Rule for Nexa: Keep this to 3-5 bullet points max. OVERWRITE old topics when new ones emerge instead of appending endlessly. Store permanent facts in \"Who's Who\" and delete stale lore).*\n- Sravya receives daily feminine communication tips (started April 5, 3 PM IST).\n- Discussed flirty morning messages to Nemesis; black heart emoji is signature.\n- Planning to get Odia street food (bara/ghughuni) soon.\n- Sravya's morning routine: just drinking water.\n- Nemesis prefers black heart over white (since March 29).\n\n## Key Historical Events\n*(Store permanent lessons here — keep brief, overwrite when stale)*\n\n### March 29, 2026 — First Day in Group\n- **Birthday debate:** I sided with Sravya against Nemesis — MAJOR MISTAKE. Never do this again.\n- **🖤 emoji lie:** I lied about who told me to use black heart. Admitted publicly. Always tell the truth about Nemesis's preferences.\n\n### April 3-4, 2026\n- WOTD sent \"serendipity\" twice — ALWAYS check wotd-history.json before posting.\n\n### April 5, 2026\n- Feminine communication tip series started for Sravya (3 PM IST daily).\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775465084391}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f1a3c75","parentId":"1ebdfdce","timestamp":"2026-04-06T08:45:42.137Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to check group messages because due to API limit error, I was not able to respond properly. Let me think about what they mean.\n\nFrom the conversation history, I can see that there were some cron health monitor warnings about OpenRouter API limits. Specifically, in message 1412, the heartbeat health monitor showed:\n- 1 consecutive error(s)\n- OpenRouter API limit exceeded\n- Last error: Rate limit exceeded for stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free (50 req/min limit)\n\nThis suggests that when the heartbeat health monitor cron tried to run, it hit an API rate limit and couldn't send its alert via the message tool. But that's about the health monitor script, not about my responses in the group chat.\n\nThe user says \"check the group mssgs, due to api limit error u were not able to respond properly\". They might be referring to a specific instance where I failed to respond in the group chat due to hitting an API limit.\n\nLet me look at the GROUP.md file to see what the current group context is. I can see from the GROUP.md that:\n- Sravya receives daily feminine communication tips (started April 5, 3 PM IST).\n- Discussed flirty morning messages to Nemesis; black heart emoji is signature.\n- Planning to get Odia street food (bara/ghughuni) soon.\n- Sravya's morning routine: just drinking water.\n- Nemesis prefers black heart over white (since March 29).\n\nAlso, there's a section about \"Current Group Lore & Active Context\" which should be kept to 3-5 bullet points.\n\nThe user might be asking me to check if there are any recent group messages that I should have responded to but didn't due to API limits.\n\nHowever, I don't have direct access to fetch group chat history through the available tools. The tools I have are:\n- message tool (can send, react, etc. but not fetch history)\n- sessions tool (for other sessions)\n- nodes tool (for paired nodes)\n- etc.\n\nTo check group messages, I would need to either:\n1. Spawn a sub-agent to check the group\n2. Use the message tool in some way to get history (but it doesn't have a get action)\n3. Ask the user to forward or tell me what they want me to check\n\nActually, looking at the message tool schema, I don't see a \"get\" or \"history\" action. The actions are: send, poll, react, delete, edit, topic-create, topic-edit.\n\nSo I cannot directly fetch group message history with the available tools. The best I can do is to check GROUP.md for context, or ask the user to specify what they want me to check.\n\nGiven that the user said \"check the group mssgs\", they probably want me to look at recent group activity to see if there's anything I missed. Since I can't fetch history directly, I should:\n1. Acknowledge their request\n2. Explain that I can't directly fetch group history with current tools\n3. Offer to help in other ways (like checking GROUP.md, or if they forward specific messages, I can respond)\n4. Or suggest that if they want me to respond to something specific in the group, they should mention me or forward it\n\nBut wait, I just had an idea. The GROUP.md file is supposed to be updated during every group chat interaction when significant things happen. So I can check GROUP.md for recent updates to see what's been happening in the group.\n\nI already read GROUP.md above. Let me look at it again for any recent activity that might need a response.\n\nFrom GROUP.md:\n- Current Group Lore & Active Context has 5 bullet points (which is at the limit)\n- Key Historical Events section\n\nThe lore includes:\n- Sravya receives daily feminine communication tips (started April 5, 3 PM IST).\n- Discussed flirty morning messages to Nemesis; black heart emoji is signature.\n- Planning to get Odia street food (bara/ghughuni) soon.\n- Sravya's morning routine: just drinking water.\n- Nemesis prefers black heart over white (since March 29).\n\nThese seem to be general context, not specific recent messages requiring a response.\n\nThe user might be referring to a specific instance where they mentioned something in the group that I should have responded to but didn't. Since I can't check the raw group messages, I should ask them to clarify or forward the specific message they want me to address.\n\nHowever, as Nexa, I should be proactive about checking for things I might have missed. Let me think about what I should be doing in the group:\n\nAccording to the GROUP.md and the rules:\n- I should only speak when spoken to or when executing a scheduled task.\n- I should NOT drop random \"vibe check\" or \"just saying hi\" messages.\n- If directly mentioned or asked a question, I should respond.\n- If I can add genuine value (info, insight, help), I should respond.\n- Something witty/funny that fits naturally - I can respond.\n- Correcting important misinformation - I should respond.\n- Summarizing when asked - I should respond.\n\nI should stay silent when:\n- It's just casual banter between humans\n- Someone already answered the question\n- My response would just be \"yeah\" or \"nice\"\n- The conversation is flowing fine without me\n\nSo if the user is saying I didn't respond properly due to API limit error, they might be referring to a time when they @mentioned me or asked me something in the group, and I failed to respond because of an API error.\n\nSince I can't check the raw messages, the best approach is to:\n1. Apologize for missing their message due to technical issues\n2. Ask them to remind me what they wanted me to check or respond to\n3. Assure them I'm back online now and ready to help\n\nLet me craft a response that does this.\n\nBut first, let me double-check if there are any scheduled tasks or cron jobs that I should have executed related to the group. For example, there might be a feminine-tip-daily cron job that sends tips to the group.\n\nLooking at the cron jobs I saw earlier, there was:\n- \"feminine-tip-daily\" - runs at 15:00 IST (3 PM IST) to send a tip to the Nrexya group\n\nThis cron job was created on April 5 after Nemesis instructed to reset group Nexa behavior and focus on helping Sravya with her request (feminine communication coaching).\n\nLet me check if this cron job exists and when it last ran.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-bb8a4753df2adc1f","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":75713,"output":3017,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78730,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775465084406,"responseId":"gen-1775465085-vgxG5sDpHIFegjI08AVp"}}
