{"type":"message","id":"a127ea63","parentId":"89fbbf65","timestamp":"2026-04-06T15:08:01.944Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1439\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-06 15:07 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\n1 Hey Nexa, I've just pushed a few architectural and stability optimizations to your workspace repository.\n 2\n 3 Please run a git pull from your workspace root (./) to fetch the latest changes.\n 4\n 5 Here's a quick summary of the updates to your operational manual:\n 6 1. Portable Paths: All hardcoded absolute paths (~/.openclaw/workspace/) in HEARTBEAT.md, CRON-CONTEXT.md, and your skills have been\n replaced with relative paths so your setup works seamlessly across any operating system.\n 7 2. Native State Persistence: Instead of running raw, verbose bash scripts for state persistence, HEARTBEAT.md now instructs you to use your\n native update_heartbeat_state skill tool for cleaner, error-free execution.\n 8 3. Dependency Standards: I've added a requirements.txt to clarify your Python dependencies and updated package.json to include standard npm\n run scripts for your health checks and verifications.\n 9\n 10 Once you've pulled, please acknowledge silently and apply these updated rules to your future heartbeat and cron operations."}],"timestamp":1775488081910}}
