{"type":"message","id":"13f1ddae","parentId":"e8398816","timestamp":"2026-04-07T02:10:20.001Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The github-backup job shows lastRunAtMs: 1775527388476 which is Tue Apr 8 2026 15:03:08 UTC? Let me check: 1775527388 seconds since epoch. Current time is Tue Apr 8 2026 02:08 UTC according to the message timestamp. Wait that doesn't make sense - the last run is in the future? Let me convert properly.\n\nActually 1775527388 seconds since Jan 1 1970 is:\nLet's calculate: 1775527388 / 86400 = 20550 days approx. 20550 days from 1970 is around year 2026? 1970 + 56 = 2026. 56*365 = 20440 days. Plus leap days ~14 = 20454. So 20550 - 20454 = 96 days into 2026. Jan 1 + 96 days = April 6. So 1775527388 seconds is around April 6, 2026. The time of day: 96 days * 86400 = 8294400 seconds. 1775527388 - 8294400 = 1767232988? That's not right.\n\nBetter: Let's use date command. I'll run: date -d @1775527388\n\nBut I can see from the state: the lastRunAtMs for github-backup is 1775527388476 ms. Divide by 1000: 1775527388.476 seconds.\n\nI know that 1775415426580 ms (from earlier) was for the heartbeat-health-monitor createdAt. That timestamp was in the past. Let me just check the current time and compare.\n\nCurrent time from the message: Tue 2026-04-07 02:08 UTC. That's April 7, 2026 at 02:08 UTC.\n\nThe github-backup lastRunAtMs: 1775527388476 ms. Let's convert to date: I'll use the exec tool.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-bc0481d615d4ecec","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"date -d @1775527388 -u"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":124122,"output":961,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125083,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775527748321,"responseId":"gen-1775527749-RI1RZZhohBQ5qBNn65TB"}}
