{"type":"message","id":"9f56cc33","parentId":"bf482a01","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:07:33.956Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to use the correct tool names. Looking at the tools list, I see:\n- `web_search` (not `web_search.search`)\n- `message` (not `message.send`)\n\nLet me fix the script to use the correct tool names. The OpenClaw gateway expects the tool name and action separately. Let me check how to properly call these tools.\n\nLooking at the working examples from earlier in the conversation, I see patterns like:\n- `web_search` with `action` parameter\n- `message` with `action` parameter\n\nActually, looking at the tool definitions:\n- `web_search` has parameters: `query`, `count`, etc.\n- `message` has parameters: `action`, `channel`, `target`, `message`, etc.\n\nBut when calling via gateway, I need to use the correct format. Let me check how the heartbeat health monitor calls web_search.\n\nLooking at the heartbeat-health-monitor cron job payload:\n```\n\"message\": \"python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/heartbeat_health_cron.py\"\n```\n\nAnd that script likely uses the tools correctly. Let me check that script to see the proper format.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a64c2e36a65a2945","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/heartbeat_health_cron.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":133933,"output":552,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134485,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775534834836,"responseId":"gen-1775534835-5cnUkKAChBZAvCs6pHHT"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8d748f4c","parentId":"9f56cc33","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:07:34.013Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a64c2e36a65a2945","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nHeartbeat Health Monitor - Cron Job\nRuns independently of the heartbeat to verify state is being updated.\nAlerts if heartbeat state becomes stale.\n\nThis should run as a cron job (recommended: every 1 hour).\nIf heartbeat state is stale, it will DM Nemesis with the alert.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 heartbeat_health_cron.py [--dry-run]\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nimport argparse\nimport re\nimport urllib.error\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSCRIPT_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent\nSTATE_FILE = SCRIPT_DIR / \"memory\" / \"heartbeat-state.json\"\nNEMESIS_ID = \"7924461837\"\n\nTHRESHOLDS = {\n    \"heartbeat_run\": {\"warning\": 45, \"critical\": 60},\n    \"group_message\": {\"warning\": 240, \"critical\": 360},\n    \"nemesis_ping\": {\"warning\": 360, \"critical\": 480},\n    \"git_push\": {\"warning\": 180, \"critical\": 360},\n    \"memory_review\": {\"warning\": 1560, \"critical\": 1800},\n}\n\nACTIVE_HOURS = {\"start\": 7, \"end\": 23}\n\n\ndef load_state():\n    if not STATE_FILE.exists():\n        return {\"lastChecks\": {}}\n    with open(STATE_FILE, \"r\") as f:\n        return json.load(f)\n\n\ndef minutes_ago(timestamp_str):\n    if not timestamp_str:\n        return None\n    try:\n        last_time = datetime.fromisoformat(timestamp_str.replace(\"Z\", \"+00:00\"))\n        now = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n        return (now - last_time).total_seconds() / 60\n    except:\n        return None\n\n\ndef is_active_hours():\n    \"\"\"Check if current IST time is within active hours (7 AM - 11 PM).\"\"\"\n    now_utc = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n    ist_offset = timedelta(hours=5, minutes=30)\n    now_ist = now_utc.astimezone(timezone(timedelta(hours=5, minutes=30)))\n    hour = now_ist.hour\n    return ACTIVE_HOURS[\"start\"] <= hour < ACTIVE_HOURS[\"end\"]\n\n\ndef check_health():\n    state = load_state()\n    last_checks = state.get(\"lastChecks\", {})\n\n    critical = []\n    warnings = []\n    active = is_active_hours()\n\n    for field, thresholds in THRESHOLDS.items():\n        value = last_checks.get(field)\n        minutes = minutes_ago(value)\n\n        if minutes is None:\n            if field == \"heartbeat_run\" and not active:\n                continue\n            critical.append(f\"{field}: Never run\")\n        elif minutes >= thresholds[\"critical\"]:\n            if field == \"heartbeat_run\" and not active:\n                continue\n            critical.append(\n                f\"{field}: CRITICAL - {round(minutes)} min since last run (threshold: {thresholds['critical']} min)\"\n            )\n        elif minutes >= thresholds[\"warning\"]:\n            warnings.append(\n                f\"{field}: WARNING - {round(minutes)} min since last run (threshold: {thresholds['warning']} min)\"\n            )\n\n    return critical, warnings\n\n\ndef keepalive_state():\n    \"\"\"Update heartbeat_run state during inactive hours to prevent stale alerts.\"\"\"\n    state = load_state()\n    now = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n    state.setdefault(\"lastChecks\", {})\n    state[\"lastChecks\"][\"heartbeat_run\"] = now\n\n    STATE_FILE.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    with open(STATE_FILE, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(state, f, indent=2)\n\n    print(\"Heartbeat keepalive: state updated (inactive hours)\")\n\n\ndef get_bot_token():\n    \"\"\"Get Telegram bot token from openclaw config.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\"openclaw\", \"config\", \"get\", \"channels.telegram.botToken\"],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n            timeout=10,\n        )\n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            token = result.stdout.strip()\n            # Remove any potential quoting or extra characters\n            token = token.strip('\"\\'')\n            if token and token != \"__OPENCLAW_REDACTED__\" and token != \"undefined\" and token != \"null\":\n                return token\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"DEBUG: Error getting bot token: {e}\")\n    return None\n\n\ndef send_telegram_message(bot_token, chat_id, text):\n    \"\"\"Send message directly via Telegram Bot API using curl.\"\"\"\n    import urllib.request\n    import urllib.parse\n\n    url = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{bot_token}/sendMessage\"\n    data = json.dumps(\n        {\n            \"chat_id\": chat_id,\n            \"text\": text,\n            \"parse_mode\": \"Markdown\",\n            \"disable_notification\": False,\n        }\n    ).encode(\"utf-8\")\n\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        url, data=data, headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}\n    )\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=15) as resp:\n            return json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        print(f\"HTTP Error {e.code}: {e.reason}\")\n        print(f\"URL: {url}\")\n        print(f\"Data: {data}\")\n        raise\n    except urllib.error.URLError as e:\n        print(f\"URL Error: {e.reason}\")\n        raise\n\n\ndef format_alert_message(critical, warnings):\n    \"\"\"Build the alert message text.\"\"\"\n    timestamp = datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M UTC\")\n    lines = [\n        f\"⚠️ **Heartbeat Health Alert** `{timestamp}`\",\n        \"\",\n    ]\n\n    if critical:\n        lines.append(\"**CRITICAL:**\")\n        for item in critical:\n            lines.append(f\"• {item}\")\n        lines.append(\"\")\n\n    if warnings:\n        lines.append(\"**Warnings:**\")\n        for item in warnings:\n            lines.append(f\"• {item}\")\n        lines.append(\"\")\n\n    lines.append(\"_Script: scripts/heartbeat_health_cron.py_\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\ndef send_alert(critical, warnings, dry_run=False):\n    \"\"\"Send alert to Nemesis via Telegram Bot API.\"\"\"\n    message = format_alert_message(critical, warnings)\n\n    if dry_run:\n        print(\"DRY RUN - Would send:\")\n        print(message)\n        return\n\n    bot_token = get_bot_token()\n    if not bot_token:\n        print(\"ERROR: Could not get Telegram bot token from config\")\n        print(\"Falling back to openclaw system event...\")\n        fallback_alert(critical, warnings)\n        return\n\n    try:\n        result = send_telegram_message(bot_token, NEMESIS_ID, message)\n        if result.get(\"ok\"):\n            print(f\"Alert sent to {NEMESIS_ID}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Telegram API error: {result.get('description', 'unknown')}\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error sending Telegram message: {e}\")\n        fallback_alert(critical, warnings)\n\n\ndef fallback_alert(critical, warnings):\n    \"\"\"Fallback: use openclaw system event to alert (will go to default channels).\"\"\"\n    message = format_alert_message(critical, warnings)\n    message = message.replace(\"*\", \"\").replace(\"_\", \"\").replace(\"`\", \"\")\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\n                \"openclaw\",\n                \"system\",\n                \"event\",\n                \"--mode\",\n                \"now\",\n                \"--text\",\n                message,\n            ],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n            timeout=30,\n        )\n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            print(\"Alert sent via system event\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"System event fallback also failed: {result.stderr}\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Fallback failed: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Heartbeat Health Monitor Cron\")\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Don't send alerts, just print\"\n    )\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    active = is_active_hours()\n\n    if not active:\n        keepalive_state()\n        print(\"Outside active hours (11 PM - 7 AM IST), state kept alive. Exiting.\")\n        sys.exit(0)\n\n    critical, warnings = check_health()\n\n    if critical or warnings:\n        print(f\"Issues found - Critical: {len(critical)}, Warnings: {len(warnings)}\")\n        for item in critical:\n            print(f\"  ✗ {item}\")\n        for item in warnings:\n            print(f\"  ⚠ {item}\")\n\n        if critical:\n            if args.dry_run:\n                send_alert(critical, warnings, dry_run=True)\n            # Return the alert message for the cron job to handle\n            alert_message = format_alert_message(critical, warnings)\n            print(f\"ALERT_MESSAGE::{alert_message}\")\n            sys.exit(2)\n    else:\n        print(\"Heartbeat state healthy\")\n        sys.exit(0)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775534853999}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1e47b0b","parentId":"8d748f4c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:08:21.090Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to fix the daily_war_update.py script to use the correct method names based on the heartbeat health monitor script I just looked at. I can see that the correct methods are:\n\nFor web search: Use `web_search.search` (based on the error message)\nFor sending messages: Use `message.send` \n\nBut the error showed that these methods are unknown. Let me check what methods are actually available by looking at how the heartbeat health monitor makes calls.\n\nActually, looking at the heartbeat health monitor, I see it doesn't make web_search or message.send calls directly - it only does state checking and sending alerts via its own mechanism. For the war update, I need to use the correct OpenClaw gateway methods.\n\nLet me check what the correct method names are by looking at existing working cron jobs. Looking at the github-backup cron job in the cron list, I see it uses a message.send call in its payload:\n\n\"message\": \"Run these commands: cd /root/.openclaw/workspace && git add -A && git diff --cached --quiet && echo \\\"nothing to commit\\\" || (git commit -m \\\"auto backup\\\" && git push). Report result to Nemesis via message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=7924461837) only if there was an error. If nothing changed, reply NO_REPLY.\"\n\nSo the correct format for sending a message is to use the message tool with action=send. And for web search, I need to use the web_search tool.\n\nLet me check how other cron jobs use these tools. Looking at the ai-news-digest cron job:\n\n\"message\": \"FIRST: Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Get today date. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md for todays context if exists. Step 1: Do a web search for latest AI news today. Step 2: Summarize 5-7 interesting AI news items in a short digestible format. Step 3: Use message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=7924461837) to send to Nemesis. Keep it short, fun, varied. If fails, message error to same target.\"\n\nSo the pattern is:\n- For web search: The description says \"Do a web search for latest AI news today\" but it doesn't show the exact command. This suggests that the web search is done implicitly by the AI when processing the prompt, or there's a different mechanism.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at these cron job payloads, they seem to be natural language instructions that the AI agent is supposed to interpret and execute, not direct tool calls. The AI reads the payload and then performs the actions described.\n\nSo for my war update script, instead of making direct tool calls, I should write it as a natural language prompt that the AI agent will interpret, similar to how the other cron jobs work.\n\nLet me rewrite the daily_war_update.py script to be a natural language prompt that the AI agent can execute, similar to the existing cron jobs.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-83cc21c99f4123a1","name":"write","arguments":{"file":"~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/daily_war_update.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDaily War Update Script - Natural language prompt for AI agent to execute\nThis script is called by cron and contains instructions for the AI agent\n\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\ndef main():\n    # Get current time for context\n    now_ist = datetime.now(timezone.utc).astimezone(timezone(timedelta(hours=5, minutes=30)))\n    date_str = now_ist.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    \n    # Create the natural language prompt for the AI agent to execute\n    prompt = f\"\"\"Today's date is {date_str}. \n\nPlease provide a comprehensive global war and conflict update for Nemesis with the following structure:\n\n**Historical Context (approximately 100 words, excluding the 24hr update):**\n- Overview of major ongoing global conflicts and tensions\n- Focus on Iran-US situation as requested\n- Include other significant conflicts worldwide\n- Brief context on how situations have evolved to current state\n\n**Last 24 Hours Developments:**\n- Key events and developments in the last 24 hours\n- Specific updates on Iran-US tensions\n- Other significant conflict zone updates\n- Any diplomatic initiatives or escalations\n\n**India-Specific Implications:**\n- How these conflicts affect India's interests\n- Predictions for future impact on India based on current trends\n- India's potential role or stance in these situations\n\n**Important Instructions:**\n- Cross-verify information using multiple sources before presenting facts\n- Keep the historical summary to approximately 100 words (not including the 24hr update section)\n- Be concise but comprehensive\n- Use clear, accessible language\n- If uncertain about any information, state the uncertainty rather than guessing\n- Format the response clearly with the section headers as shown above\n\nPlease execute this request and send the result to Nemesis via Telegram message.\"\"\"\n\n    # Send this prompt as an agentTurn to be processed by the AI\n    # We'll use the openclaw gateway to create an agent turn\n    result = subprocess.run([\n        \"openclaw\", \"cron\", \"add\",\n        \"--job\", json.dumps({\n            \"name\": \"daily-war-update-execution\",\n            \"schedule\": {\"kind\": \"every\", \"everyMs\": 1000},  # Run once after 1 second\n            \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n            \"payload\": {\n                \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n                \"message\": prompt\n            },\n            \"delivery\": {\n                \"mode\": \"announce\",\n                \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n                \"to\": \"7924461837\"\n            }\n        })\n    ], capture_output=True, text=True)\n    \n    if result.returncode != 0:\n        print(f\"Failed to create execution job: {result.stderr}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    else:\n        print(\"War update execution job created successfully\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":136063,"output":2031,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138094,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775534854014,"responseId":"gen-1775534854-fqV10IEOJjf3G432CL6O"}}
