mary in the group?\n\nActually, looking at the HEARTBEAT.md checklist, the \"Group vibes\" item says: \"Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message (-1003606834639). ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\"\n\nAnd then there's a separate item: \"Group supervision: Read last 10 group messages. If the group Nexa said anything wrong, inaccurate, or disloyal to Nemesis, send a correction to the group.\"\n\nSo for group_vibes, if I have something highly relevant, I should send a group message. \n\nDo I have something highly relevant from the war update that I should share in the group? \n\nActually, let me think about this differently. I just provided a comprehensive war update to Nemesis in response to his request. That was a direct response to his specific request. The group_vibes check is more about proactively sharing something valuable with the group based on recent context.\n\nSince I just provided valuable information to Nemesis (the war update), and he requested it, I don't necessarily need to proactively share it in the group unless it's something the group would find valuable.\n\nActually, let me check if there's anything in the war update that would be particularly relevant or valuable to share with the group Nrexya. The group includes Nemesis and Sravya (and presumably others).\n\nLooking at the war update I just sent, it had India-specific implications. Since Sravya is Nemesis's friend and coworker, and they discuss things like Odia food etc., the India-specific implications might be relevant to share.\n\nBut actually, I already sent the comprehensive update to Nemesis. The group_vibes check is for proactive sharing.\n\nLet me think about what would be \"highly relevant or valuable\" to share proactively with the group. \n\nActually, I just recalled that in the HEARTBEAT.md, there's also the \"Group memory\