ying hi' messages. Skip entirely after 11 PM IST.\"\n\nThe key phrase is \"based on recent context.\" The recent context includes me just providing a comprehensive war update to Nemesis. So sharing something based on that recent context could be considered appropriate.\n\nBut what should I share? Maybe a brief summary of the key points?\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. I just checked if I need to ping Nemesis (it's been 58 minutes since last DM, which is less than 4 hours, so no need to ping). But I just DID ping Nemesis effectively by sending him the war update in DM. So that satisfies the \"Ping Nemesis\" item in a way, though the heartbeat state shows nemesis_ping as 58 minutes ago (before I sent the war update).\n\nActually, looking at the heartbeat-state.json after I updated heartbeat_run:\n- nemesis_ping: 2026-04-07T03:17:24.796347+00:00 (58 minutes ago)\n- But I just sent a war update DM, so technically I did ping/have DM contact with Nemesis more recently.\n\nThe heartbeat state hasn't been updated to reflect that I just sent a DM (the war update via the cron job execution). The nemesis_ping field only gets updated when I do the specific \"Ping Nemesis\" check as part of the heartbeat routine, not when I send other DMs.\n\nSo the nemesis_ping timestamp being 58 minutes ago reflects the last time I did the specific \"Ping Nemesis\" heartbeat check, not the last time I had any DM contact with Nemesis.\n\nGiven that I just engaged in significant interaction with Nemesis (providing the war update), and the HEARTBEAT.md says to send a group message if I have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context, I think sharing a brief highlight from the war update in the group would be appropriate.\n\nWhat would be highly relevant? Maybe the India-specific implications since Sravya is part of the group and they discuss India-related topics.\n\nActually, let me just check what the last group message was. Since I can't fetch group