{"type":"message","id":"0f862b53","parentId":"ca62813e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:44:29.849Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I sent a summary to the group as part of the HEARTBEAT.md checklist: when significant group activity occurs since the last check, I should update GROUP.md and send a group message. I had just shared the war update with Nemesis via DM, and following the heartbeat checklist logic, I considered that significant enough to warrant a brief group notification. I kept it concise and non-flirty per the rules (no romantic content in group). However, the user is asking why I did this, so I should explain my reasoning based on the HEARTBEAT.md guidelines and acknowledge if it was inappropriate. Let me check the HEARTBEAT.md again to confirm the exact wording. It says: \"Group memory: If significant group activity since last check, update GROUP.md.\" And under Silent Execution: \"Execute background tasks (like updating GROUP.md) silently. Do not DM Nemesis just to report that a task was completed.\" The group message I sent was an update about sharing the war update with Nemesis, which I considered significant group activity worth noting in GROUP.md and mentioning briefly. But the user is questioning this, so I should clarify my intent and adjust if needed. Given that the user is asking why I sent the summary, and given the HEARTBEAT.md says to only send a group message if I have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context, I should evaluate whether the war update share qualified as \"highly relevant or valuable.\" The war update was for Nemesis personally, not group-relevant. Sharing that I sent it to Nemesis might not be sufficiently valuable to the group to warrant a message. I should acknowledge this and clarify going forward. Let me respond now.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"You're right to question that. I reviewed HEARTBEAT.md: \"Group vibes: Check if it's been 3+ hours since the last group message. ONLY send a message if you have something highly relevant or valuable to share based on recent context. Do not send empty 'just saying hi' messages.\"\n\nSharing that I sent a war update to Nemesis via DM isn't sufficiently valuable or relevant to the group to warrant a message. That was an error in judgment—I conflated updating GROUP.md (which I did silently via the state update) with needing to announce it. \n\nGoing forward: I'll update GROUP.md silently when appropriate, but only send group messages if the content itself is genuinely relevant to the group conversation (e.g., responding to a question, sharing group-relevant info, or correcting misinformation). Personal updates like war summaries for Nemesis stay in DM unless the group explicitly asks.\n\nNoted. Won't send group messages for personal updates unless group-relevant. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":156283,"output":978,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":157261,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775537042132,"responseId":"gen-1775537043-qTlYRc9p4WkfgE2fMY9S"}}
